cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new optimization strategy for improving the generalization performance of deep learning models. The experiments conducted in the paper involve several computer vision tasks such as image classification (cs.CV) and language modeling (cs.CL), which also make these sub-categories likely. Additionally, the use of adaptive optimization methods such as Adam and the investigation of their limitations and drawbacks suggest that the paper could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the focus on optimization techniques for deep learning models and the use of neural networks in the experiments make the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category a possibility as well.
